      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Hello, this is 6 Minute English from BBC Learning English. I'm Neil.And I'm Rob.Now I'm sure most of us have interacted with a chatbot. These are bits of computer technology that respond to text with text or respond to your voice. You ask it a question and usually it comes up with an answer.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:10.558238",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"BI\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "ce569d8f-1620-4bc1-8601-ca67164309b6",
      "chunk_index": 1,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766d3",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Should we fear chatbots_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "We'll discuss that more in a moment and find out if chatbots really think for themselves. But first I have a question for you, Rob. The first computer program that allowed some kind of plausible conversation between humans and machines was invented in 1966.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:10.560705",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "fad66f64-5901-4891-aa7e-f9d6fa4e12bf",
      "chunk_index": 2,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766d3",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Should we fear chatbots_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "But what was it called? Was it A. Alexa B. Eliza or C. Parry? Well, it's not Alexa. That's too new. So I'll guess C. Parry. I'll reveal the answer at the end of the program. Now, the old chatbots of the 1960s and 70s were quite basic. But more recently, the technology is able to predict the next word that is likely to be used in a sentence and it learns",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:10.563244",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"UI\", \"LED\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "f41578e3-7f18-452c-a586-294f82124c2b",
      "chunk_index": 3,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766d3",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
