      "episode_title": "Should we fear chatbots_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Radio 4 programme Word of Mouth.Emily M. Bender, Professor of Computational Linguistics at the University of Washington explained why it's dangerous to always trust what a chatbot is telling us.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:10.568192",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"RSI\", \"UI\", \"XP\", \"AI\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "5c70c58f-9167-413a-a8d5-62d569c693c4",
      "chunk_index": 5,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766d3",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Should we fear chatbots_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Yes, chatbots might appear to write in this way but really they are just predicting one word after another based on what they have learnt. We should therefore be on guard. Be careful and alert about the accuracy of what we are being told.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:10.570595",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "48a4e274-e917-402d-98bb-7b840b309f60",
      "chunk_index": 6,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766d3",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Should we fear chatbots_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "A cognitive psychologist and computer scientist called Geoffrey Hinton",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:10.572740",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"LED\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "b83b8973-582e-43d4-9a14-8618a7b4d6b5",
      "chunk_index": 7,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766d3",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
